<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm14291568">
<term>cost-plus regulation</term><meaning id="fs-idp23015104">when regulators permit a regulated firm to cover its costs and to make a normal level of profit</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm160678352">
<term>price cap regulation</term><meaning id="fs-idm99678720">when the regulator sets a price that a firm cannot exceed over the next few years</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

